scp:
To use the scp command to copy a file from a remote host to your local machine, you can use the following syntax:

syntax:
scp [options] [user}@[host]:[source_file] [destination]


[options]: Optional command-line options that modify the behavior of scp.
[user]@[host]: The username and hostname or IP address of the remote server.
[source_file]: The path to the file on the remote server that you want to copy.
[destination]: The path where you want to save the copied file on your local machine.
